Detailed Description

Format of the second result word and subsequent result words written by the hardware.

uint64_t cvmx_dfa_result1_t::extra_bits_high

If PASS3 or CN58XX and DFA_CFG[NRPL_ENA] == 1 and IWORD0[Ty] == 1, then set to <27:24> of the last next-node pointer.

Else set to 0x0.

uint64_t cvmx_dfa_result1_t::extra_bits_low

If PASS3 or CN58XX and DFA_CFG[NRPL_ENA] == 1 and IWORD0[Ty] == 1, then set to <23:22> of the last next-node pointer.

Else set to 0x0.

uint64_t cvmx_dfa_result1_t::next_node_repl

If PASS3 or CN58XX and DFA_CFG[NRPL_ENA] == 1 and IWORD0[Ty] == 1, then set to next_node_repl (<21:20>) of the last next-node pointer.

Else set to 0x0.

Index of the previous node.
